1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:19,930
[ Watch on kissasia.li ]

2
00:00:19,959 --> 00:00:22,169
[theme music playing]

3
00:00:58,664 --> 00:00:59,498
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

4
00:00:59,582 --> 00:01:01,083
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY
WITH SUPERVISION

5
00:01:20,853 --> 00:01:22,021
[Soo-jin] Si-woo.

6
00:01:26,358 --> 00:01:29,361
[soft pop music playing]

7
00:01:36,076 --> 00:01:38,412
-[Ji-yoon] Why are they…
-[chuckles]

8
00:01:39,330 --> 00:01:40,497
[chuckles]

9
00:01:41,999 --> 00:01:45,127
Did they choose
to stay friends after breaking up?

10
00:01:46,587 --> 00:01:47,713
Shall we?

11
00:01:49,298 --> 00:01:50,132
Sure.

12
00:01:55,721 --> 00:01:59,099
[Ji-yoon] But why am I feeling this way?

13
00:01:59,183 --> 00:02:00,225
[sighs]

14
00:02:04,939 --> 00:02:05,940
[chuckles]

15
00:02:07,441 --> 00:02:10,319
This feels so awkward,
just having tea together.

16
00:02:11,278 --> 00:02:12,655
Congratulations.

17
00:02:13,405 --> 00:02:14,281
Hmm.

18
00:02:15,407 --> 00:02:17,743
You were shocked that I asked to see you.

19
00:02:17,826 --> 00:02:18,911
What's this about?

20
00:02:18,994 --> 00:02:22,831
Remember the first thing I said
when I ran into you again at SAEUM?

21
00:02:22,915 --> 00:02:25,834
I do. You said, "Nice to meet you."

22
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:30,965
I wanted to bury our personal history
and keep things strictly professional.

23
00:02:31,048 --> 00:02:32,216
That makes two of us.

24
00:02:32,299 --> 00:02:34,551
I want to stop pretending we're strangers.

25
00:02:36,637 --> 00:02:39,848
You know there are many rumors
circulating about you, right?

26
00:02:40,891 --> 00:02:41,767
I'm used to it.

27
00:02:42,768 --> 00:02:43,644
And I don't care.

28
00:02:44,228 --> 00:02:46,021
That's good, but it went a bit too far.

29
00:02:47,022 --> 00:02:49,566
I'm glad Young-hun
posted on the company forum.

30
00:02:50,150 --> 00:02:50,985
Thank you.

31
00:02:52,111 --> 00:02:53,195
Hmm?

32
00:02:53,278 --> 00:02:56,281
Did you contact him
after what Mr. Ko said?

33
00:02:56,365 --> 00:02:57,199
It wasn't me.

34
00:03:04,748 --> 00:03:06,000
Did you see your photo at the game?

35
00:03:06,083 --> 00:03:07,668
There was a photo?

36
00:03:07,751 --> 00:03:08,752
[scoffs]

37
00:03:19,805 --> 00:03:22,266
I feel things must've been really tough
for Ms. Cha.

38
00:03:22,933 --> 00:03:26,353
First, everyone made a huge fuss
about her dating her boss,

39
00:03:26,437 --> 00:03:29,106
then they turned her
into some victim being exploited.

40
00:03:29,189 --> 00:03:31,442
I had no idea about this.

41
00:03:31,525 --> 00:03:32,651
Ji-yoon…

42
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:35,195
I care a lot about her, okay?

43
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:39,116
Besides,
she's your one and only team member.

44
00:03:42,161 --> 00:03:45,080
I just wouldn't like
to see either of you get hurt.

45
00:03:55,174 --> 00:03:57,801
[Ji-yoon] If you got married
and then divorced,

46
00:03:57,885 --> 00:03:59,845
what would you call your ex-husband?

47
00:03:59,928 --> 00:04:01,805
Why would I even talk to him?

48
00:04:01,889 --> 00:04:04,516
What is this, Hollywood? [scoffs]

49
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:08,228
If I saw so much as the back
of Goo-won's head, my blood would boil.

50
00:04:08,312 --> 00:04:11,648
[chuckles] You could end up
working at the same company.

51
00:04:11,732 --> 00:04:13,692
Ugh, I don't wanna think about that.

52
00:04:13,776 --> 00:04:16,153
Couples who aren't married change jobs
quickly after a breakup.

53
00:04:16,236 --> 00:04:19,073
-Imagine after a divorce.
-[chuckles] That's true.

54
00:04:20,824 --> 00:04:24,328
Also, sweetly calling each other
by their first names.

55
00:04:24,411 --> 00:04:26,413
There's a couple like that at our company?

56
00:04:26,497 --> 00:04:29,083
Uh, no. It was on Blah Blah.

57
00:04:31,418 --> 00:04:33,045
I guess it's one of two things.

58
00:04:33,128 --> 00:04:35,214
Either they have no feelings
for each other,

59
00:04:35,297 --> 00:04:37,841
or there's still something going on
between them.

60
00:04:37,925 --> 00:04:38,926
Then…

61
00:04:39,927 --> 00:04:43,263
Then what does it mean if seeing them
like that makes your heart pound?

62
00:04:43,347 --> 00:04:44,848
They said that on Blah Blah?

63
00:04:45,432 --> 00:04:46,475
Yeah. Mm-hmm.

64
00:04:47,434 --> 00:04:49,019
Maybe…

65
00:04:50,729 --> 00:04:52,689
-they have a crush?
-It's not that!

66
00:04:54,733 --> 00:04:57,528
Um, I mean… I'm sure.

67
00:04:58,153 --> 00:04:59,905
Let me see. I'll read it myself.

68
00:04:59,988 --> 00:05:02,407
Oh. It was deleted right away.

69
00:05:02,491 --> 00:05:04,868
-Mm-hmm.
-[phone buzzing]

70
00:05:06,328 --> 00:05:07,371
Hi, Na-ri.

71
00:05:08,413 --> 00:05:09,248
A what?

72
00:05:10,207 --> 00:05:11,208
Just a moment.

73
00:05:12,543 --> 00:05:14,711
Wanna go to a group blind date?

74
00:05:16,171 --> 00:05:17,464
-Ms. Cha.
-Hmm?

75
00:05:18,715 --> 00:05:20,092
-Mm-hmm.
-Mmm.

76
00:05:21,552 --> 00:05:22,761
She says yes.

77
00:05:22,845 --> 00:05:23,846
Hmm?

78
00:05:23,929 --> 00:05:28,892
EPISODE 5
HAVE A "MEETING," STILL CLOCKING IN!

79
00:05:28,976 --> 00:05:30,602
I already said no!

80
00:05:31,562 --> 00:05:34,481
I'm not planning on dating anytime soon.

81
00:05:34,565 --> 00:05:35,649
It's not a date.

82
00:05:35,732 --> 00:05:38,193
It's just doing something different
to have some fun.

83
00:05:38,277 --> 00:05:42,364
[sighs] Listen. I just don't have
the mental bandwidth

84
00:05:42,447 --> 00:05:43,782
for that right now, okay?

85
00:05:43,866 --> 00:05:45,993
What, is there something going on
with Mr. Kang?

86
00:05:46,076 --> 00:05:49,705
[gasps] Hey! No way.
There's nothing going on.

87
00:05:49,788 --> 00:05:52,708
I mean, aren't you guys
starting a new project?

88
00:05:54,293 --> 00:05:56,170
Oh, yeah. That's right.

89
00:05:56,253 --> 00:05:58,172
There's nothing yet.

90
00:05:58,255 --> 00:06:00,007
-[chuckles]
-[phone buzzes]

91
00:06:02,593 --> 00:06:05,220
[Si-woo] We'll start our afternoon
schedule in the product showroom.

92
00:06:05,304 --> 00:06:07,639
Looks like it's starting,
our next project.

93
00:06:07,723 --> 00:06:09,516
[chuckles] I'll see you.

94
00:06:10,475 --> 00:06:12,186
Well, give it some more thought!

95
00:06:14,354 --> 00:06:18,150
What if someone saw them
being so informal to each other?

96
00:06:18,233 --> 00:06:20,611
Well, no wonder I was freaking out.

97
00:06:20,694 --> 00:06:21,695
[scoffs]

98
00:06:22,654 --> 00:06:24,907
[gasps] Mr. Kang?

99
00:06:26,825 --> 00:06:28,076
Is he sleeping?

100
00:06:47,721 --> 00:06:50,724
[tender music playing]

101
00:07:11,036 --> 00:07:12,579
[No-ah] Maybe…

102
00:07:13,914 --> 00:07:14,998
they have a crush?

103
00:07:16,917 --> 00:07:18,752
[Ji-yoon] Do I? Mr. Kang?

104
00:07:27,511 --> 00:07:29,263
That can't be it.

105
00:07:30,013 --> 00:07:33,267
To me, he's just someone I work with.

106
00:07:41,900 --> 00:07:45,821
His face is definitely my type though.

107
00:07:53,829 --> 00:07:55,956
Is that a citrus scent?

108
00:08:05,173 --> 00:08:06,008
[gasps]

109
00:08:09,594 --> 00:08:10,554
[gasps]

110
00:08:16,310 --> 00:08:17,853
I missed it.

111
00:08:17,936 --> 00:08:19,438
What did you miss?

112
00:08:20,272 --> 00:08:21,440
The mosquito.

113
00:08:24,443 --> 00:08:25,819
Where did it go?

114
00:08:25,902 --> 00:08:27,404
[mosquito buzzing sound plays]

115
00:08:27,487 --> 00:08:28,488
[gasps]

116
00:08:28,572 --> 00:08:30,574
[comical music playing]

117
00:08:31,825 --> 00:08:33,035
[sighs]

118
00:08:54,765 --> 00:08:56,016
[clears throat]

119
00:08:56,516 --> 00:09:00,270
So, going forward, what kind of products
would you like to make?

120
00:09:00,354 --> 00:09:01,938
The ideas I had in my notebook

121
00:09:02,022 --> 00:09:05,817
have either been made
or are currently being developed.

122
00:09:05,901 --> 00:09:09,571
I would really love if my appliances could
read my mind

123
00:09:09,654 --> 00:09:12,032
and work on their own
when I get home from work.

124
00:09:14,034 --> 00:09:16,995
Let's make that our next project. Home-AI.

125
00:09:17,079 --> 00:09:18,413
Home AI?

126
00:09:18,497 --> 00:09:20,540
Yes. Our next project

127
00:09:20,624 --> 00:09:24,336
will be focused on delivering
an advanced user experience using AI,

128
00:09:24,419 --> 00:09:25,712
as a team reporting to the President.

129
00:09:25,796 --> 00:09:28,006
Directly to the President…

130
00:09:28,090 --> 00:09:28,924
in the States?

131
00:09:29,007 --> 00:09:31,343
It's a project I've been planning
alongside the President

132
00:09:31,426 --> 00:09:32,636
since I was in the States.

133
00:09:32,719 --> 00:09:36,181
So the reason the task force
was formed in the first place…

134
00:09:36,264 --> 00:09:38,517
Was to bring this project to completion.

135
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:42,854
Wow. I guess nothing happens by accident
in this company, huh?

136
00:09:42,938 --> 00:09:45,941
The Development Team and I
will handle the technical side of things.

137
00:09:46,024 --> 00:09:48,860
Ms. Cha, you'll create the scenarios.

138
00:09:48,944 --> 00:09:51,238
I need you to imagine the user's lifestyle

139
00:09:51,321 --> 00:09:53,949
to anticipate what they'll need
in different situations,

140
00:09:54,032 --> 00:09:55,409
and build a narrative around that.

141
00:09:57,828 --> 00:09:59,079
That sounds like fun.

142
00:09:59,663 --> 00:10:01,915
[gentle music playing]

143
00:10:04,292 --> 00:10:06,336
I guess you aren't scared
of failing anymore.

144
00:10:06,420 --> 00:10:07,254
Sorry?

145
00:10:07,337 --> 00:10:10,173
When I first asked you to join
the task force, you said,

146
00:10:11,049 --> 00:10:13,093
"I'm scared of failing right now.

147
00:10:13,844 --> 00:10:16,430
I'd like to work on something
with a higher chance of success."

148
00:10:16,513 --> 00:10:20,058
But now, I've gotten a taste of success.

149
00:10:20,725 --> 00:10:23,937
And I want to succeed again
together with you, sir.

150
00:10:25,355 --> 00:10:27,983
However, I'm a little nervous,

151
00:10:28,066 --> 00:10:29,568
as it's something I've never done.

152
00:10:29,651 --> 00:10:31,486
Doing what you know is comfortable,

153
00:10:31,570 --> 00:10:34,072
but it's also easy to fall into a rut.

154
00:10:34,156 --> 00:10:37,951
Taking on new challenges
sparks a fresh dose of inspiration.

155
00:10:40,203 --> 00:10:42,330
Being in a relationship you know
is comfortable,

156
00:10:42,414 --> 00:10:44,332
but it's easy to fall into a rut.

157
00:10:44,416 --> 00:10:48,753
Taking on a man of mystery
will spark a fresh dose of inspiration.

158
00:10:55,510 --> 00:10:58,972
I don't think it should
just be the two of us anymore.

159
00:10:59,806 --> 00:11:01,349
Well, I guess that you're right.

160
00:11:03,310 --> 00:11:04,895
Because it's a major project…

161
00:11:04,978 --> 00:11:07,355
Then we'll run
a second round of recruitment.

162
00:11:08,190 --> 00:11:09,024
Right.

163
00:11:16,156 --> 00:11:18,033
[thunder rumbles]

164
00:11:19,117 --> 00:11:21,328
-That's not right.
-I told you I don't wanna talk to you!

165
00:11:21,411 --> 00:11:22,787
[Ji-yoon] Oh.

166
00:11:24,206 --> 00:11:25,540
I'm sorry, sir.

167
00:11:34,216 --> 00:11:36,885
I know the rumors about
me putting you in a tough spot.

168
00:11:36,968 --> 00:11:38,887
Oh! No, sir. Not at all.

169
00:11:38,970 --> 00:11:40,972
If anything like that happens again,

170
00:11:41,723 --> 00:11:43,183
tell me. I'll be more careful.

171
00:11:49,648 --> 00:11:51,066
The storm cloud is gone.

172
00:11:51,691 --> 00:11:52,567
Storm cloud?

173
00:11:53,318 --> 00:11:56,488
There was a storm cloud
hovering over your head.

174
00:11:56,571 --> 00:11:58,281
[thunder rumbling]

175
00:11:58,365 --> 00:11:59,824
[rain pattering]

176
00:11:59,908 --> 00:12:01,493
Oh. That's rain.

177
00:12:07,123 --> 00:12:08,333
[chuckles]

178
00:12:09,626 --> 00:12:10,460
[clears throat]

179
00:12:11,586 --> 00:12:14,005
Wait here a moment.
I'll go get an umbrella.

180
00:12:14,089 --> 00:12:16,841
Why? I'm having so much fun.

181
00:12:18,218 --> 00:12:20,220
I don't remember the last time
I ran through the rain.

182
00:12:22,013 --> 00:12:23,723
Wanna make a bet on who gets there first?

183
00:12:25,308 --> 00:12:26,518
Ready…

184
00:12:29,354 --> 00:12:31,189
Go! [chuckling]

185
00:12:31,273 --> 00:12:35,443
[soft pop music playing]

186
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:09,185
Did you see it? The post?

187
00:13:09,269 --> 00:13:10,854
Oh, yeah.

188
00:13:11,354 --> 00:13:13,106
FUTURE HOUSEHOLD APPLIANCES TASK FORCE
SECOND ROUND

189
00:13:13,773 --> 00:13:14,941
[sighs]

190
00:13:15,525 --> 00:13:17,319
-Ms. Yoon No-ah.
-Yes?

191
00:13:18,194 --> 00:13:20,697
Is this garbage the best you could do
for your executive report?

192
00:13:20,780 --> 00:13:24,367
Have you actually learned anything
from Ms. Cha? Honestly.

193
00:13:24,451 --> 00:13:25,869
Geez.

194
00:13:28,079 --> 00:13:31,124
Every one of you,
please go get your act together!

195
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:33,460
[Young-sam sighs]

196
00:13:36,296 --> 00:13:37,297
[sniffles]

197
00:13:38,798 --> 00:13:41,343
He was fine for a while.
What's gotten into him now?

198
00:13:41,843 --> 00:13:44,554
What do you think?
It's because of the task force again.

199
00:13:45,930 --> 00:13:47,223
Hey, it's me.

200
00:13:48,433 --> 00:13:50,852
Uh, how about
the team leads grab a drink tonight?

201
00:13:51,645 --> 00:13:52,729
Want revenge?

202
00:13:53,313 --> 00:13:54,147
What?

203
00:13:54,773 --> 00:13:57,025
They say you should enjoy life
after you get revenge.

204
00:13:57,108 --> 00:13:59,361
FUTURE HOUSEHOLD APPLIANCES TASK FORCE
SECOND ROUND

205
00:14:01,321 --> 00:14:02,530
[sighs]

206
00:14:09,663 --> 00:14:11,122
How is it all going?

207
00:14:11,206 --> 00:14:14,584
The team leads agreed to use this chance
to get rid of the thorn in our sides.

208
00:14:14,668 --> 00:14:16,961
Hey. You still don't get that guy, huh?

209
00:14:17,045 --> 00:14:19,005
Why do you think
he caught the President's eye?

210
00:14:19,089 --> 00:14:22,258
Throwing a few bad apples into the mix
isn't going to cut it.

211
00:14:22,342 --> 00:14:24,344
[tense music playing]

212
00:14:25,970 --> 00:14:29,057
If we wanna bring the task force down,
we go after the head.

213
00:14:29,140 --> 00:14:30,392
By "head," you mean…

214
00:14:30,475 --> 00:14:31,643
[lighter clicks]

215
00:14:32,686 --> 00:14:33,728
[blows]

216
00:14:34,938 --> 00:14:37,607
Dig into Kang Si-woo.
I'm sure you'll find something.

217
00:14:38,566 --> 00:14:39,442
Sure.

218
00:14:50,912 --> 00:14:53,164
There are a lot of applicants.

219
00:14:53,248 --> 00:14:55,750
All the rumors about Mr. Kang
have been debunked

220
00:14:55,834 --> 00:14:58,044
and Cha Ji-yoon totally nailed it there.

221
00:14:59,254 --> 00:15:00,547
And it's AI.

222
00:15:00,630 --> 00:15:02,298
Are you going to apply?

223
00:15:02,382 --> 00:15:03,842
You know quite a bit about AI.

224
00:15:03,925 --> 00:15:08,096
That's a luxury I can't afford with twins
and a wife working three shifts.

225
00:15:09,180 --> 00:15:10,098
And you?

226
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:11,683
Aren't you interested?

227
00:15:11,766 --> 00:15:13,101
[sighs]

228
00:15:13,685 --> 00:15:16,646
Every time Mr. Ko
starts his ridiculous nitpicking,

229
00:15:16,730 --> 00:15:18,398
I wanna quit on the spot.

230
00:15:18,481 --> 00:15:21,609
But I don't feel confident
applying without strong achievements.

231
00:15:22,277 --> 00:15:24,154
And I still find Mr. Kang intimidating.

232
00:15:24,237 --> 00:15:25,488
Well, he is.

233
00:15:26,364 --> 00:15:28,992
Even more so,
now that we know he's completely clean.

234
00:15:31,578 --> 00:15:33,788
[No-ah sighs]

235
00:15:33,872 --> 00:15:34,789
Thank you, sir.

236
00:15:36,291 --> 00:15:38,460
[sighs] This is harder than I thought.

237
00:15:38,543 --> 00:15:42,046
Some were pushed into applying,
rather than doing so willingly.

238
00:15:43,214 --> 00:15:44,215
[knocks on door]

239
00:15:47,844 --> 00:15:48,762
Ms. Na-ri!

240
00:15:49,846 --> 00:15:52,432
Hello! I am Shin Na-ri
of the Marketing Team.

241
00:15:52,515 --> 00:15:53,683
Please take a seat.

242
00:15:58,396 --> 00:16:00,398
May I ask why you decided to apply?

243
00:16:00,482 --> 00:16:03,777
Well, can I be completely honest
with the two of you?

244
00:16:03,860 --> 00:16:06,237
-Sure.
-I'm being kicked out.

245
00:16:06,321 --> 00:16:07,280
Why?

246
00:16:07,363 --> 00:16:09,491
I'm the "Three-Why-Girl," you see.

247
00:16:09,574 --> 00:16:10,658
By "three why,"

248
00:16:10,742 --> 00:16:13,453
do you mean, "Why me? Why this? But why?"

249
00:16:13,536 --> 00:16:16,539
Yes. It's just a habit of mine.

250
00:16:16,623 --> 00:16:20,376
Oh, but my team lead said
they'd had enough and told me to

251
00:16:20,460 --> 00:16:22,796
go to the task force
and do whatever I wanted.

252
00:16:22,879 --> 00:16:24,881
[chuckles] And what happened this time?

253
00:16:24,964 --> 00:16:27,717
Thing is… they told me
to take on a boring project

254
00:16:27,801 --> 00:16:30,053
I was against in the first place.

255
00:16:30,136 --> 00:16:31,638
There was nothing fresh about it,

256
00:16:31,721 --> 00:16:33,765
and we still went ahead with it anyway.

257
00:16:34,474 --> 00:16:35,517
So I said,

258
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:38,353
"Why me? Why this? But why?"

259
00:16:38,978 --> 00:16:39,979
And that's that.

260
00:16:40,563 --> 00:16:41,564
[Na-ri chuckles]

261
00:16:42,065 --> 00:16:44,025
I can't stand doing anything predictable.

262
00:16:44,651 --> 00:16:46,486
Were you wearing that when you said it?

263
00:16:49,405 --> 00:16:52,033
-Lost your touch…
-[gasps]

264
00:16:52,116 --> 00:16:55,036
…"Lost your touch, damn it"?

265
00:16:55,119 --> 00:16:56,704
How did you know that?

266
00:16:57,497 --> 00:17:01,918
You're actually the first superior
to understand how I feel.

267
00:17:02,001 --> 00:17:03,878
Some people have no eye for talent.

268
00:17:03,962 --> 00:17:05,213
You're right.

269
00:17:13,179 --> 00:17:15,223
We won't be needing any more meetings.

270
00:17:15,306 --> 00:17:16,266
Please cancel the rest.

271
00:17:16,349 --> 00:17:17,433
Sorry?

272
00:17:17,517 --> 00:17:19,102
What about expanding the team?

273
00:17:19,185 --> 00:17:21,104
I'll handle the team-building myself.

274
00:17:21,187 --> 00:17:22,981
Oh. Okay.

275
00:17:24,274 --> 00:17:26,234
And I'm taking a half day off today.

276
00:17:26,317 --> 00:17:27,569
Why?

277
00:17:28,903 --> 00:17:31,573
For personal reasons.
Do I have to share them with you?

278
00:17:31,656 --> 00:17:32,907
No.

279
00:17:34,742 --> 00:17:36,411
Of course not. No.

280
00:18:01,019 --> 00:18:03,229
You should clock out early too, Ms. Cha.

281
00:18:03,938 --> 00:18:04,772
Okay.

282
00:18:04,856 --> 00:18:06,524
And don't drink too much coffee.

283
00:18:07,567 --> 00:18:10,194
[chuckles] This is chamomile tea.

284
00:18:10,278 --> 00:18:11,112
That's good.

285
00:18:15,533 --> 00:18:18,953
[scoffs]
Who's he meeting that he even got flowers?

286
00:18:25,585 --> 00:18:27,754
Does it really have a calming effect?

287
00:18:35,845 --> 00:18:38,097
[sighs] No way.

288
00:18:40,391 --> 00:18:42,226
-Oh, my gosh!
-[gasps]

289
00:18:42,310 --> 00:18:44,395
[chuckles] Why are you so startled?

290
00:18:44,479 --> 00:18:45,521
Oh, Ms. Choi.

291
00:18:46,105 --> 00:18:48,149
Ah. Could you wait here for just a minute?

292
00:18:52,403 --> 00:18:54,447
-Have you had lunch? [chuckles]
-Huh? Yes.

293
00:18:54,530 --> 00:18:55,698
[sighs]

294
00:18:57,283 --> 00:18:59,285
What on earth was I expecting?

295
00:19:00,161 --> 00:19:01,955
Pfft. She just got married!

296
00:19:06,834 --> 00:19:08,503
A little wedding favor.

297
00:19:08,586 --> 00:19:09,921
Thanks for taking the time to come.

298
00:19:10,004 --> 00:19:12,590
Oh, but you really didn't have to,
Ms. Choi.

299
00:19:12,674 --> 00:19:16,427
-What? You don't consider me close enough?
-No, that's not what I'm saying.

300
00:19:16,511 --> 00:19:19,138
-[chuckles]
-Thank you so much.

301
00:19:19,222 --> 00:19:20,974
Anyway, how's the task force?

302
00:19:21,057 --> 00:19:23,393
To be honest, it can be quite tough,

303
00:19:23,476 --> 00:19:25,019
but it is also lots of fun.

304
00:19:25,103 --> 00:19:26,187
"Lots of fun"?

305
00:19:26,270 --> 00:19:29,399
[scoffs] Wait, has your team lead
brainwashed you?

306
00:19:29,482 --> 00:19:31,025
[chuckles]

307
00:19:31,109 --> 00:19:33,778
-Maybe. [chuckles]
-[chuckles]

308
00:19:33,861 --> 00:19:36,823
Ah, that Kang Si-woo… [clicks tongue]

309
00:19:37,532 --> 00:19:40,326
It won't be easy,
but you'll learn a lot from him.

310
00:19:40,410 --> 00:19:41,536
Yeah.

311
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:44,247
I'm learning a lot from him.

312
00:19:44,330 --> 00:19:45,623
Sometimes,

313
00:19:46,207 --> 00:19:51,421
he tends to brood alone and ends up making
the person next to him feel lonely.

314
00:19:51,504 --> 00:19:53,297
[calm piano music playing]

315
00:19:53,381 --> 00:19:54,799
Whenever that happens,

316
00:19:55,550 --> 00:19:57,176
you just have to give him time.

317
00:19:59,012 --> 00:20:01,347
You seem to know a lot about him.

318
00:20:01,431 --> 00:20:04,225
Isn't he actually pretty easy to read?
[chuckles]

319
00:20:04,308 --> 00:20:06,144
At least he doesn't say things
he doesn't mean.

320
00:20:06,227 --> 00:20:07,395
[chuckles]

321
00:20:08,271 --> 00:20:11,899
Far better than Mr. Ko,
who's always scheming, right?

322
00:20:11,983 --> 00:20:14,110
Yes. [chuckles]

323
00:20:14,193 --> 00:20:16,654
So, go and have lots of fun!

324
00:20:17,238 --> 00:20:19,532
If things get tough, just come see me.

325
00:20:19,615 --> 00:20:20,533
Sure.

326
00:20:20,616 --> 00:20:21,951
I'm off. Good luck.

327
00:20:22,035 --> 00:20:23,119
Yeah. Thank you.

328
00:20:29,125 --> 00:20:30,585
[sighs]

329
00:20:36,257 --> 00:20:38,217
BIRTH, JULY 11, 1962 SEO YUN-HEE
DEATH, AUGUST 22, 2014

330
00:21:00,198 --> 00:21:01,616
It's been three years.

331
00:21:02,617 --> 00:21:03,493
Yes.

332
00:21:04,410 --> 00:21:07,622
How did you find living in the States?

333
00:21:07,705 --> 00:21:09,665
Didn't feel any different from here.

334
00:21:13,419 --> 00:21:16,547
Have you been well, Father?

335
00:21:17,048 --> 00:21:20,301
Seeing as I'm not with your mom yet,

336
00:21:21,219 --> 00:21:22,053
I guess I have.

337
00:21:40,822 --> 00:21:42,031
I'll see you outside.

338
00:21:55,837 --> 00:21:56,796
You should head home.

339
00:21:59,048 --> 00:22:02,426
I'm thinking of selling the house
and moving to the countryside.

340
00:22:04,220 --> 00:22:05,221
Why so suddenly?

341
00:22:06,347 --> 00:22:08,099
I'm fed up with everything.

342
00:22:09,016 --> 00:22:12,395
Today feels like yesterday,
and yesterday like today.

343
00:22:13,229 --> 00:22:15,648
Old memories just keep getting more vivid.

344
00:22:16,149 --> 00:22:18,526
[chuckles]
I've been in that house for too long.

345
00:22:20,403 --> 00:22:23,781
I'm not sure where I'll move yet,
but it'll be hard for me to come.

346
00:22:23,865 --> 00:22:25,908
See if you can match my schedule.

347
00:22:25,992 --> 00:22:29,370
If not, we may have to visit separately.

348
00:22:29,453 --> 00:22:31,747
I might not be here next year.

349
00:22:35,209 --> 00:22:36,794
I may move back to the States.

350
00:22:37,795 --> 00:22:38,963
[sighs]

351
00:22:46,929 --> 00:22:49,432
[grunting]

352
00:22:50,975 --> 00:22:52,393
Here. Take this.

353
00:22:54,812 --> 00:22:55,980
[gentle music playing]

354
00:22:56,063 --> 00:22:57,231
This is…

355
00:22:57,857 --> 00:23:01,235
Yeah. It's the one you took apart, broke,

356
00:23:01,319 --> 00:23:03,404
and then secretly fixed.

357
00:23:03,487 --> 00:23:04,739
You knew that?

358
00:23:04,822 --> 00:23:06,574
Wait until you have children.

359
00:23:07,658 --> 00:23:09,493
We just pretend that we don't know.

360
00:23:10,828 --> 00:23:12,246
But you loved this thing.

361
00:23:12,330 --> 00:23:13,915
I don't need it now.

362
00:23:14,582 --> 00:23:17,335
I haven't used it once
since your mom passed.

363
00:23:17,418 --> 00:23:20,129
Throw it away, fix it. It's up to you.

364
00:23:32,058 --> 00:23:33,559
I have nothing to report.

365
00:23:34,101 --> 00:23:35,937
There's nothing urgent.

366
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:38,898
[scoffs] I don't have a single question.

367
00:23:38,981 --> 00:23:42,526
[sighs] I don't have a single excuse
to call him. Ugh.

368
00:23:43,819 --> 00:23:45,279
-[sighs]
-[phone buzzes]

369
00:23:45,363 --> 00:23:47,365
[upbeat music playing]

370
00:23:49,075 --> 00:23:50,660
APPLY FOR RATE BENEFITS AND RECEIVE
PREFERENTIAL RATES ON LOAN!

371
00:23:51,994 --> 00:23:54,997
Wow, looks like
they'll offer loans to just anyone.

372
00:23:55,081 --> 00:23:56,874
[door bells chiming]

373
00:24:31,117 --> 00:24:34,787
[scoffs] It wouldn't hurt you
to tell me where you're going. Hmm.

374
00:24:35,496 --> 00:24:38,374
But you had to leave me
wondering all day. [scoffs]

375
00:24:39,417 --> 00:24:40,293
Oh?

376
00:24:41,085 --> 00:24:42,628
I still have some left.

377
00:24:43,254 --> 00:24:44,964
[sniffs] Ugh.

378
00:24:45,715 --> 00:24:47,133
[sighs]

379
00:24:49,010 --> 00:24:52,054
It'd be nice if a fridge
told you expiration dates.

380
00:24:54,015 --> 00:24:55,224
Hmm.

381
00:25:00,062 --> 00:25:01,814
[device chimes]

382
00:25:01,897 --> 00:25:03,566
APPLICATION
NAME: SHIN NA-RI

383
00:25:03,649 --> 00:25:04,859
Next.

384
00:25:10,656 --> 00:25:12,408
It's acting up again.

385
00:25:12,491 --> 00:25:13,409
WOULD YOU LIKE TO DELETE THIS?

386
00:25:13,492 --> 00:25:14,785
No.

387
00:25:16,871 --> 00:25:17,830
Just…

388
00:25:19,373 --> 00:25:20,750
just hide it out of sight.

389
00:25:31,135 --> 00:25:32,762
TIME SAVING, ENERGY EFFICIENCY,
PERSONALIZED CARE

390
00:25:37,975 --> 00:25:40,644
KANG SI-WOO

391
00:25:40,728 --> 00:25:42,438
KANG SI-WOO

392
00:25:42,521 --> 00:25:45,566
[lighthearted music playing]

393
00:25:53,032 --> 00:25:54,200
[sighs]

394
00:25:54,283 --> 00:25:55,576
He's not on here.

395
00:25:58,371 --> 00:25:59,246
Figures.

396
00:26:00,289 --> 00:26:03,125
Why would he?
Mr. Kang is older than me, so…

397
00:26:04,710 --> 00:26:06,337
[bebop music playing]

398
00:26:06,420 --> 00:26:07,671
KANG SI-WOO

399
00:26:10,132 --> 00:26:11,133
[gasps]

400
00:26:11,801 --> 00:26:12,927
Why so many?

401
00:26:17,556 --> 00:26:18,849
KANG SI-WOO HANKUK UNIVERSITY,
MECHANICAL ENGINEERING

402
00:26:19,725 --> 00:26:20,643
KANG SI-WOO
NO POSTS

403
00:26:29,235 --> 00:26:30,444
SAEUM HALL OF FAME

404
00:26:30,528 --> 00:26:31,904
2020 BEST HOME APPLIANCE GRAND PRIZE

405
00:26:31,987 --> 00:26:33,447
KANG SI-WOO, THE DRIVING FORCE
BEHIND THE TASK FORCE'S SUCCESS

406
00:26:40,496 --> 00:26:42,123
He's even more impressive

407
00:26:42,998 --> 00:26:44,208
than I thought.

408
00:26:44,291 --> 00:26:45,835
DEGREE IN MECHANICAL ENGINEERING
FROM HANKUK UNIVERSITY

409
00:26:50,214 --> 00:26:52,508
HANKUK UNIVERSITY
MECHANICAL ENGINEERING 06

410
00:27:01,767 --> 00:27:04,019
ENTREPRENEURIAL PASSION!
STARTUP "NIKKE"!

411
00:27:04,103 --> 00:27:05,312
[gasps] Found him.

412
00:27:09,442 --> 00:27:13,279
[laughing]

413
00:27:13,362 --> 00:27:16,323
Oh, what is this? So dated.

414
00:27:19,368 --> 00:27:20,327
[gasps]

415
00:27:20,411 --> 00:27:21,662
8:12 P.M.

416
00:27:21,745 --> 00:27:23,414
Oh, I'm insane.

417
00:27:23,956 --> 00:27:24,957
[groans]

418
00:27:34,842 --> 00:27:36,802
[gentle music playing]

419
00:27:46,479 --> 00:27:48,522
What am I even doing?

420
00:28:05,873 --> 00:28:08,042
Fine. I'll do it.

421
00:28:08,125 --> 00:28:09,376
The group blind date.

422
00:28:12,671 --> 00:28:13,672
[sighs]

423
00:28:14,173 --> 00:28:15,174
[phone buzzes]

424
00:28:22,848 --> 00:28:24,517
[No-ah] Okay, I'll let Na-ri know!

425
00:28:26,644 --> 00:28:28,354
[sighs]

426
00:28:31,065 --> 00:28:33,317
This place is worth the price.

427
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:35,194
-Let's clink glasses.
-Sure. [chuckles]

428
00:28:35,277 --> 00:28:37,363
[classical piano music playing]

429
00:28:41,951 --> 00:28:43,285
Mmm. Delicious.

430
00:28:43,369 --> 00:28:46,038
Let's bring Goo-won here next time.

431
00:28:46,121 --> 00:28:50,292
Our Dr. Kim is so busy lately,
he won't even answer his mother's calls.

432
00:28:51,460 --> 00:28:54,004
What? He's not doing well?
Is he eating properly?

433
00:28:54,088 --> 00:28:55,839
I honestly don't know, ma'am.

434
00:28:55,923 --> 00:28:57,633
Why? Did you two fight?

435
00:28:57,716 --> 00:28:58,968
Uh, no.

436
00:28:59,677 --> 00:29:00,636
Of course.

437
00:29:01,303 --> 00:29:03,639
We broke up, actually.

438
00:29:05,140 --> 00:29:05,975
Gosh.

439
00:29:06,058 --> 00:29:08,811
Couples fight all the time. That's normal.

440
00:29:08,894 --> 00:29:10,938
You just have to let him win this time.

441
00:29:11,021 --> 00:29:13,399
[clicks tongue]
You know he's going through a lot.

442
00:29:14,024 --> 00:29:16,151
That's why I even begged on my knees.

443
00:29:16,652 --> 00:29:18,654
But he said no, saying he met someone.

444
00:29:19,363 --> 00:29:20,239
What?

445
00:29:20,823 --> 00:29:21,657
Wait…

446
00:29:22,199 --> 00:29:24,118
-What kind of girl?
-[scoffs]

447
00:29:25,619 --> 00:29:27,663
Is that what you want to know?

448
00:29:28,372 --> 00:29:30,916
Why? To see
if she looks better on paper than me?

449
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:31,875
Hey!

450
00:29:32,626 --> 00:29:34,712
How could you say such a thing?

451
00:29:34,795 --> 00:29:38,549
I'm just worried that Goo-won might have
fallen for a dubious girl. [sighs]

452
00:29:38,632 --> 00:29:41,176
Don't worry.
She's a student from his med school.

453
00:29:43,137 --> 00:29:44,138
So ma'am…

454
00:29:45,389 --> 00:29:48,058
could you please talk some sense into him?

455
00:29:51,437 --> 00:29:53,981
[sighs] Should've just stuck to the plan.

456
00:29:54,607 --> 00:29:55,774
You know what he's like.

457
00:29:55,858 --> 00:29:58,235
Once Goo-won makes up his mind,

458
00:29:58,319 --> 00:30:00,237
there's no way you can get him to listen.

459
00:30:00,321 --> 00:30:03,866
So you want me to just back off
so Kim Goo-won and that girl

460
00:30:03,949 --> 00:30:05,451
can live happily ever after?

461
00:30:05,534 --> 00:30:07,620
Why would you say that?

462
00:30:08,120 --> 00:30:09,371
I'm just trying to tell you

463
00:30:09,455 --> 00:30:12,791
to go find a better man
since I think of you as a daughter.

464
00:30:13,375 --> 00:30:15,919
Do you really think anything I say
will change his mind?

465
00:30:16,003 --> 00:30:17,004
No, ma'am.

466
00:30:18,505 --> 00:30:20,507
You can't come
and treat me like this either.

467
00:30:21,258 --> 00:30:23,761
Not after everything
I've done for Goo-won.

468
00:30:23,844 --> 00:30:26,513
Because I trusted
we were going to get married anyway,

469
00:30:26,597 --> 00:30:29,350
I bought everything,
from the appliances to the furniture.

470
00:30:29,433 --> 00:30:31,644
And that bag you brought today?

471
00:30:31,727 --> 00:30:33,187
That was my entire month's salary, ma'am.

472
00:30:33,270 --> 00:30:34,897
[scoffs] Wait.

473
00:30:35,939 --> 00:30:37,524
You did all that because you wanted to.

474
00:30:37,608 --> 00:30:40,986
Is that why you called me every time
something happened to Goo-won?

475
00:30:41,070 --> 00:30:44,323
And all the talks about marriage
and asking me to look after him?

476
00:30:44,406 --> 00:30:45,783
[huffs] Geez.

477
00:30:45,866 --> 00:30:48,243
You're incredibly rude, aren't you?

478
00:30:52,081 --> 00:30:52,915
Excuse me.

479
00:30:53,916 --> 00:30:56,377
I'm very sorry to interrupt
your lovely evening, ma'am.

480
00:30:58,379 --> 00:31:01,965
But I've fallen for your daughter
at first sight.

481
00:31:03,133 --> 00:31:05,094
[breathes shakily] She's not my daughter.

482
00:31:05,177 --> 00:31:06,804
I promise I'm not some creep.

483
00:31:13,936 --> 00:31:15,187
[chuckles]

484
00:31:17,523 --> 00:31:18,440
If you're a lawyer,

485
00:31:18,524 --> 00:31:21,944
you must know all about
what constitutes marriage fraud.

486
00:31:22,027 --> 00:31:22,861
Of course.

487
00:31:22,945 --> 00:31:24,238
Then could you give me some legal advice?

488
00:31:24,321 --> 00:31:25,906
No-ah!

489
00:31:26,865 --> 00:31:28,575
I'd be happy to.

490
00:31:32,621 --> 00:31:33,664
[sighs]

491
00:31:35,457 --> 00:31:36,917
Wait. [sighs]

492
00:31:40,796 --> 00:31:42,840
You can pick up the bill for once.

493
00:31:42,923 --> 00:31:45,926
After all, I'm the idiot
who wasted seven years with your son.

494
00:31:52,641 --> 00:31:53,600
[scoffs]

495
00:31:56,687 --> 00:31:58,647
[breathing heavily]

496
00:32:06,822 --> 00:32:07,823
[No-ah sighs]

497
00:32:07,906 --> 00:32:09,825
So this revenge plan was a bust.

498
00:32:09,908 --> 00:32:10,743
Why?

499
00:32:10,826 --> 00:32:12,828
I did it. She paid an expensive meal.

500
00:32:12,911 --> 00:32:14,747
Revenge needs to be cold.

501
00:32:14,830 --> 00:32:16,457
If you get emotional, then you lose.

502
00:32:16,540 --> 00:32:18,792
But it's just so infuriating.

503
00:32:18,876 --> 00:32:22,463
Now that she found a replacement,
she's telling me to get lost.

504
00:32:22,546 --> 00:32:23,547
[scoffs]

505
00:32:24,131 --> 00:32:27,426
-And whose business card was that?
-It was my uncle's.

506
00:32:28,010 --> 00:32:30,637
We'll have to take a head-on approach.
This method won't cut it.

507
00:32:30,721 --> 00:32:32,556
[groans] Forget it, I'm tired.

508
00:32:33,557 --> 00:32:36,685
What am I doing,
taking advice from a kid? [sighs]

509
00:32:36,769 --> 00:32:38,187
[phone buzzing]

510
00:32:38,270 --> 00:32:39,480
KIM GOO-WON

511
00:32:44,568 --> 00:32:45,611
What?

512
00:32:45,694 --> 00:32:47,780
[Goo-won] What did you say to my mom?

513
00:32:47,863 --> 00:32:49,782
What on earth did you say
to make her cry, huh?

514
00:32:49,865 --> 00:32:50,866
What?

515
00:32:52,910 --> 00:32:54,912
Hey, you piece of shit!

516
00:32:54,995 --> 00:32:58,415
If you're gonna call me for this,
then go to hell!

517
00:32:58,499 --> 00:33:00,167
Ugh! [exclaims]

518
00:33:00,250 --> 00:33:02,586
-[whistles]
-[panting]

519
00:33:02,669 --> 00:33:04,630
What's the head-on approach?

520
00:33:05,339 --> 00:33:06,757
A three-way clash.

521
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:07,674
Huh?

522
00:33:07,758 --> 00:33:10,302
That girl also deserves to know
what kind of jerk he is.

523
00:33:12,971 --> 00:33:14,598
Then what was that about

524
00:33:14,681 --> 00:33:17,935
the "enjoy your life
after getting your revenge" thing?

525
00:33:19,061 --> 00:33:20,062
Ugh, never mind.

526
00:33:20,646 --> 00:33:24,233
[clicks tongue] I keep asking a kid
for advice. [sighs]

527
00:33:24,316 --> 00:33:27,069
It's about riding the rolling waves
and having fun.

528
00:33:29,446 --> 00:33:31,990
Doing what you want without being scared.

529
00:33:32,074 --> 00:33:33,450
Isn't that enjoying life?

530
00:33:38,247 --> 00:33:39,998
On that note, wanna go surfing?

531
00:33:47,923 --> 00:33:51,009
MY BOYFRIEND'S TEACHING ME SURFING
THIS WEEKEND! WHAT SHOULD I WEAR?

532
00:33:52,219 --> 00:33:53,595
#DATINGASOFTODAY #HEARTHEART
#DAILY #LOVESTAGRAM #LOVEYOU

533
00:33:53,679 --> 00:33:54,680
[sighs]

534
00:33:55,848 --> 00:33:56,807
Well…

535
00:33:57,933 --> 00:33:59,476
the thing is, I…

536
00:33:59,977 --> 00:34:00,811
You scared?

537
00:34:01,645 --> 00:34:03,939
-I'm going on a group blind date!
-Group date?

538
00:34:04,022 --> 00:34:07,609
Yes… [chuckles] …I might be busy
this weekend because of it.

539
00:34:07,693 --> 00:34:09,027
That's why…

540
00:34:10,362 --> 00:34:11,280
I can't go.

541
00:34:11,363 --> 00:34:12,364
[TA scoffing]

542
00:34:18,036 --> 00:34:20,163
NEW HOME-AI SCENARIO PROPOSAL

543
00:34:25,377 --> 00:34:26,587
[sighs]

544
00:34:27,671 --> 00:34:30,257
PROPOSAL BACKGROUND
CONSUMER NEEDS ANALYSIS

545
00:34:30,340 --> 00:34:32,217
So you already put this together?

546
00:34:32,301 --> 00:34:35,304
I wanted a draft before
considering the technical limitations.

547
00:34:35,387 --> 00:34:37,890
Uh, purely from
a consumer's point of view.

548
00:34:39,057 --> 00:34:40,267
By pulling an all-nighter?

549
00:34:40,350 --> 00:34:43,353
Nothing is better
than work to clear your head.

550
00:34:46,648 --> 00:34:47,858
Right. It's great work.

551
00:34:47,941 --> 00:34:50,527
The thing about AI

552
00:34:50,611 --> 00:34:54,114
is that it's not something
you can see, like a refrigerator.

553
00:34:54,197 --> 00:34:57,910
So there may be limitations
in expanding the consumer experience.

554
00:34:57,993 --> 00:34:59,620
It'd be great to have a dedicated lab.

555
00:35:00,829 --> 00:35:03,832
We have a dedicated lab already.

556
00:35:03,916 --> 00:35:04,833
We do?

557
00:35:05,417 --> 00:35:06,293
Where at?

558
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:08,420
Is it in the R&D building?

559
00:35:08,503 --> 00:35:10,297
-Would you like to see it?
-Yes.

560
00:35:11,256 --> 00:35:12,841
[comical music playing]

561
00:35:12,925 --> 00:35:13,884
Basically…

562
00:35:14,968 --> 00:35:19,056
you're saying the dedicated lab
is your home.

563
00:35:19,765 --> 00:35:22,684
We still need to keep things under wraps.

564
00:35:22,768 --> 00:35:24,144
I hope you understand.

565
00:35:24,770 --> 00:35:25,771
Sure.

566
00:35:27,189 --> 00:35:29,483
But I'm not so sure
it's okay for me to go.

567
00:35:31,401 --> 00:35:32,361
It's just for work.

568
00:35:32,444 --> 00:35:33,612
That's right.

569
00:35:34,821 --> 00:35:37,366
I'm just going there for work.

570
00:35:39,701 --> 00:35:40,535
[sighs]

571
00:35:40,619 --> 00:35:43,580
If you feel uncomfortable,
we can always do this next--

572
00:35:43,664 --> 00:35:44,665
No.

573
00:35:45,749 --> 00:35:47,125
It's for work anyway.

574
00:35:48,001 --> 00:35:50,921
As long as you're okay with it,
then I'm fine too.

575
00:35:52,214 --> 00:35:53,215
Okay.

576
00:36:13,735 --> 00:36:15,737
[tango music playing]

577
00:36:23,495 --> 00:36:24,496
Whoa.

578
00:36:28,917 --> 00:36:31,211
Tango? You like it?

579
00:36:31,294 --> 00:36:32,254
Yes.

580
00:36:32,337 --> 00:36:34,339
I recall you listening to rock.

581
00:36:34,423 --> 00:36:36,925
I'm surprised
you're into such passionate music.

582
00:36:37,009 --> 00:36:37,926
You find that shocking?

583
00:36:38,010 --> 00:36:42,556
I thought that you were the type that
just liked classical music. [chuckles]

584
00:36:48,103 --> 00:36:49,104
Hmm?

585
00:36:50,022 --> 00:36:51,148
What is that?

586
00:36:53,150 --> 00:36:54,526
What are you referring to?

587
00:36:54,609 --> 00:36:57,112
I mean, how come there's a desk
in your living room?

588
00:36:57,195 --> 00:36:58,864
The living room's the most spacious.

589
00:36:58,947 --> 00:37:00,073
Exactly.

590
00:37:00,157 --> 00:37:02,993
Why is there a desk
at the center of your home?

591
00:37:03,076 --> 00:37:04,870
Work's the center of my life.

592
00:37:06,621 --> 00:37:10,500
-Is that really so strange?
-Uh, no.

593
00:37:11,334 --> 00:37:12,461
[machine whirring]

594
00:37:13,211 --> 00:37:14,337
Oh.

595
00:37:14,421 --> 00:37:18,008
I see that you set the vacuum to run
when you get home.

596
00:37:18,091 --> 00:37:19,760
[Si-woo] It's in scanning mode.

597
00:37:19,843 --> 00:37:20,802
Sorry?

598
00:37:21,762 --> 00:37:24,222
It's the first time
it detected another person here.

599
00:37:34,107 --> 00:37:37,694
It's a prototype in development,
so it still needs a lot of tweaks.

600
00:37:39,488 --> 00:37:41,531
And it crashes frequently
for unknown reasons.

601
00:37:41,615 --> 00:37:42,616
ROBOT VACUUM CLEANER
SCANNING

602
00:37:45,494 --> 00:37:47,204
May I take a look at it?

603
00:37:47,788 --> 00:37:48,997
The beta app is on here,

604
00:37:49,706 --> 00:37:51,208
so go ahead and take a look.

605
00:37:51,291 --> 00:37:52,876
I'll get tea ready in the meantime.

606
00:37:52,959 --> 00:37:53,835
Okay.

607
00:38:00,008 --> 00:38:01,301
[sighs]

608
00:38:03,095 --> 00:38:04,638
[sucks teeth] Is this it?

609
00:38:06,098 --> 00:38:07,474
-[robot vacuum whirs]
-Oh.

610
00:38:13,063 --> 00:38:15,774
[sighs] It'd be nice if it could talk too.

611
00:38:16,691 --> 00:38:18,693
[lighthearted music playing]

612
00:38:54,729 --> 00:38:59,025
Well, I think it crashes 'cause
it handles too many functions on its own.

613
00:38:59,109 --> 00:39:01,361
It has a home cam, sensors,

614
00:39:01,444 --> 00:39:03,989
voice recognition,
and a projector function.

615
00:39:04,990 --> 00:39:06,867
Shouldn't we off-load some of them?

616
00:39:06,950 --> 00:39:08,493
Right, I'll give it some thought.

617
00:39:08,577 --> 00:39:09,619
And on that note,

618
00:39:09,703 --> 00:39:12,247
I'd like to explore case five
I presented to you.

619
00:39:12,330 --> 00:39:14,708
"The lifestyle of a man
in his mid-thirties

620
00:39:14,791 --> 00:39:16,626
who's single and living alone."

621
00:39:18,628 --> 00:39:22,465
Oh, he's also a workaholic
like that robot vacuum,

622
00:39:22,549 --> 00:39:27,053
and a self-care perfectionist who
follows a strict diet and workout plan.

623
00:39:36,605 --> 00:39:38,607
[upbeat music playing]

624
00:39:45,405 --> 00:39:48,950
WELCOME BACK HOME

625
00:39:49,534 --> 00:39:50,619
What is this?

626
00:39:51,286 --> 00:39:54,080
It's nice to have someone greet you
when you get home.

627
00:39:54,789 --> 00:39:56,166
"Welcome home."

628
00:40:00,962 --> 00:40:04,424
And when movement is detected,
the lights adjust accordingly…

629
00:40:04,507 --> 00:40:05,675
LIKES VARIOUS GENRES OF MUSIC
AMBIENT LIGHTING

630
00:40:12,891 --> 00:40:13,850
Excuse me.

631
00:40:20,357 --> 00:40:22,734
How come a bed
is the only thing in your room?

632
00:40:22,817 --> 00:40:23,902
Because I just sleep in here.

633
00:40:23,985 --> 00:40:25,862
But you could watch videos in bed

634
00:40:25,946 --> 00:40:28,949
or roll around reading comics
while eating some snacks too.

635
00:40:29,032 --> 00:40:30,408
Eating snacks in bed?

636
00:40:30,492 --> 00:40:31,868
That's simply unacceptable.

637
00:40:46,174 --> 00:40:47,759
[pop music playing]

638
00:40:49,970 --> 00:40:50,971
[sighs]

639
00:40:51,054 --> 00:40:52,764
Eating snacks in bed?

640
00:40:52,847 --> 00:40:54,349
That's simply unacceptable.

641
00:41:05,235 --> 00:41:08,071
So, are you planning to replace dinner
with these snacks?

642
00:41:08,154 --> 00:41:09,781
No, how about fried chicken?

643
00:41:09,864 --> 00:41:13,159
That's the trifecta of high-fructose
corn syrup, gluten, and trans fats.

644
00:41:13,243 --> 00:41:14,577
All of which I detest.

645
00:41:23,586 --> 00:41:26,631
[Ji-yoon sighs] It's that citrus scent.

646
00:41:28,633 --> 00:41:31,344
-Should I get changed too?
-No.

647
00:41:31,428 --> 00:41:34,180
There's no need.
We'll skip getting changed.

648
00:41:34,264 --> 00:41:35,140
Let's keep moving.

649
00:41:43,189 --> 00:41:45,150
CLEAN BEDROOM
CITRUS FRAGRANCE

650
00:41:51,364 --> 00:41:55,410
After I change into comfortable clothes,
I go to the kitchen to have a simple meal.

651
00:41:56,578 --> 00:42:00,373
Don't tell me your fridge is full of
sparkling water and not much else.

652
00:42:04,294 --> 00:42:07,839
Wow. Now that's an epic plot twist.

653
00:42:07,922 --> 00:42:09,382
[Si-woo] I don't like eating out.

654
00:42:09,466 --> 00:42:11,676
I prefer eating at home,
whenever possible.

655
00:42:13,219 --> 00:42:14,512
Are you a good cook?

656
00:42:15,263 --> 00:42:16,890
I can't say I am, but I enjoy it.

657
00:42:20,226 --> 00:42:23,188
Once I finish eating,
I put the dishes to wash,

658
00:42:23,271 --> 00:42:24,856
and brew some Pu-erh tea.

659
00:42:24,939 --> 00:42:26,649
-Want a cup?
-Sure.

660
00:42:32,489 --> 00:42:33,698
Thank you.

661
00:42:34,282 --> 00:42:37,577
A MAN WHO COOKS
PREFERS TEA OVER COFFEE

662
00:42:42,040 --> 00:42:43,249
After I drink my tea,

663
00:42:43,333 --> 00:42:46,252
I sit there and work
until it's time for bed.

664
00:42:53,176 --> 00:42:55,053
Is work all he does at home?

665
00:42:56,221 --> 00:42:57,597
Oh, that's grim.

666
00:42:59,933 --> 00:43:02,227
Oh, this is…

667
00:43:02,310 --> 00:43:05,605
That's none of your business.

668
00:43:06,189 --> 00:43:08,274
[Ji-yoon] But this is incredibly valuable.

669
00:43:08,358 --> 00:43:10,735
You can't just leave it
lying around like this.

670
00:43:15,365 --> 00:43:16,491
Wow.

671
00:43:17,951 --> 00:43:19,327
Does this belong to you?

672
00:43:19,411 --> 00:43:23,248
My parents bought it from an antique store
when they were traveling in Germany.

673
00:43:23,331 --> 00:43:26,292
You're saying they carried
this heavy thing all the way from there?

674
00:43:26,376 --> 00:43:27,210
Yeah.

675
00:43:27,710 --> 00:43:30,296
My mother often told me
about how much of a hassle it was.

676
00:43:31,589 --> 00:43:32,674
No wonder.

677
00:43:32,757 --> 00:43:36,594
This brand was discontinued long ago,
so it's hard to find in Korea.

678
00:43:36,678 --> 00:43:39,139
It's about 50 years old, I would say.

679
00:43:39,931 --> 00:43:42,934
-But does it still work?
-I haven't tried connecting it yet.

680
00:43:43,435 --> 00:43:46,271
But it seems you know a lot about stereos.

681
00:43:46,354 --> 00:43:47,355
Well…

682
00:43:48,273 --> 00:43:51,609
Someone close to me
is completely obsessed with stereos.

683
00:43:53,194 --> 00:43:56,448
[chuckles] And no,
it's not my ex-boyfriend.

684
00:43:56,948 --> 00:43:58,992
-Right.
-[chuckles]

685
00:44:13,840 --> 00:44:15,216
There's no whiteboard.

686
00:44:15,967 --> 00:44:18,011
So, what do you use these for?

687
00:44:31,107 --> 00:44:33,318
CHA JI-YOON

688
00:44:36,237 --> 00:44:38,448
[gentle music playing]

689
00:44:42,202 --> 00:44:44,287
[robot vacuum whirring]

690
00:44:47,957 --> 00:44:50,210
[beeping, static]

691
00:45:12,065 --> 00:45:16,027
CHA JI-YOON
SHE MAKES ME LAUGH

692
00:45:16,736 --> 00:45:17,654
What does…

693
00:45:18,655 --> 00:45:19,781
that mean?

694
00:45:24,452 --> 00:45:26,412
It's just a random combination of words.

695
00:45:29,249 --> 00:45:31,251
SCANNING

696
00:45:37,632 --> 00:45:38,883
You can just ignore it.

697
00:45:46,349 --> 00:45:47,225
So…

698
00:45:49,769 --> 00:45:52,188
do I really make you laugh?

699
00:46:09,247 --> 00:46:11,040
[devices chiming]

700
00:46:13,334 --> 00:46:16,421
HEART RATE IS HIGH

701
00:46:16,504 --> 00:46:18,298
CLOCK OUT!

702
00:46:20,258 --> 00:46:22,051
That's my clock-out alarm.

703
00:46:23,845 --> 00:46:24,929
Let's wrap things up,

704
00:46:26,014 --> 00:46:26,848
and call it a day.

705
00:46:26,931 --> 00:46:28,349
All right, then.

706
00:46:28,433 --> 00:46:29,475
I should get going.

707
00:46:38,526 --> 00:46:39,527
[sighs]

708
00:47:05,094 --> 00:47:06,554
[sighs]

709
00:47:09,641 --> 00:47:10,516
So, I…

710
00:47:12,518 --> 00:47:15,188
make Mr. Kang laugh?

711
00:47:17,982 --> 00:47:19,901
[gasps] What does that even mean?

712
00:47:30,703 --> 00:47:31,704
[sighs]

713
00:47:34,749 --> 00:47:41,464
CHA JI-YOON

714
00:47:55,353 --> 00:47:56,354
Hello, sir.

715
00:47:57,063 --> 00:47:58,690
-Please take a seat.
-Thank you.

716
00:48:05,405 --> 00:48:07,407
Let me get straight to the point.

717
00:48:07,490 --> 00:48:10,535
Did you apply to the task force
because of its members?

718
00:48:11,285 --> 00:48:12,620
Uh…

719
00:48:14,956 --> 00:48:17,041
I don't think
I can deny that's the reason.

720
00:48:18,251 --> 00:48:19,669
I'd like to hear more details.

721
00:48:19,752 --> 00:48:23,923
Ms. Cha told me the task force
has a great driver,

722
00:48:24,006 --> 00:48:27,093
so you just need to step on the gas
without having to worry about

723
00:48:27,176 --> 00:48:29,804
whether you're headed
in the right direction.

724
00:48:29,887 --> 00:48:32,473
So I'd like to meet a great driver too.

725
00:48:32,557 --> 00:48:35,560
Better yet, I'd like my values
to be more recognized.

726
00:48:38,229 --> 00:48:40,565
It seems Ms. Cha has got it all wrong.

727
00:48:41,190 --> 00:48:42,024
Sir?

728
00:48:42,692 --> 00:48:44,902
Ms. Cha is not the gas pedal.

729
00:48:44,986 --> 00:48:46,487
She is yet another driver.

730
00:48:47,238 --> 00:48:48,990
I see.

731
00:48:49,657 --> 00:48:50,783
I appreciate your time though.

732
00:48:51,492 --> 00:48:52,577
I'll be in touch.

733
00:49:00,543 --> 00:49:04,464
Single-person homes make up
36% of all households,

734
00:49:04,547 --> 00:49:07,550
so I think we should target
that demographic specifically.

735
00:49:07,633 --> 00:49:08,551
What do you think?

736
00:49:09,844 --> 00:49:10,678
Mr. Kang?

737
00:49:12,054 --> 00:49:13,139
Let's do that.

738
00:49:13,723 --> 00:49:16,434
We'll wrap up today's meeting here.

739
00:49:35,953 --> 00:49:37,497
Did you have something to tell me?

740
00:49:38,539 --> 00:49:40,750
Our bus will arrive in 17 minutes.

741
00:49:40,833 --> 00:49:41,834
Ah…

742
00:49:42,877 --> 00:49:45,004
The thing is,
I have plans tonight, Mr. Kang.

743
00:49:45,087 --> 00:49:46,130
Please go ahead without me.

744
00:49:51,052 --> 00:49:52,720
[whispering] I'll wait for you outside.

745
00:49:53,346 --> 00:49:54,430
Go. It's okay.

746
00:50:00,478 --> 00:50:03,564
[normal] We made plans to hang out after
work already. [chuckles]

747
00:50:03,648 --> 00:50:05,650
-What do you guys have planned?
-Sorry?

748
00:50:07,735 --> 00:50:09,153
Why does he want to know?

749
00:50:09,237 --> 00:50:11,322
He didn't tell me anything when I asked.

750
00:50:11,405 --> 00:50:14,075
What did you do
when you took that half-day off?

751
00:50:19,330 --> 00:50:21,290
It was the anniversary
of my mother's death.

752
00:50:21,374 --> 00:50:23,918
-I went to the columbarium.
-Oh.

753
00:50:25,086 --> 00:50:26,254
I'm so sorry, sir.

754
00:50:26,337 --> 00:50:28,297
Now it's your turn to tell me.

755
00:50:32,051 --> 00:50:34,136
A meeting.

756
00:50:35,596 --> 00:50:37,890
Is there a meeting I wasn't aware of?

757
00:50:37,974 --> 00:50:39,684
Well, not that kind of meeting.

758
00:50:40,893 --> 00:50:42,019
It's a group date

759
00:50:42,687 --> 00:50:45,606
where men and women get together. Meeting.

760
00:50:50,069 --> 00:50:52,238
I should've given you
more work to do then.

761
00:50:56,033 --> 00:50:56,868
Sorry?

762
00:50:58,661 --> 00:51:01,122
Enjoy your date or "meeting."

763
00:51:15,094 --> 00:51:18,306
I was nervous as hell
sitting right across from Mr. Kang.

764
00:51:18,389 --> 00:51:21,058
[groans] I don't remember
a thing that I said.

765
00:51:21,142 --> 00:51:23,394
Wait. Did he mention anything to you?

766
00:51:24,645 --> 00:51:27,064
I should've given you
more work to do then.

767
00:51:30,318 --> 00:51:31,569
Ms. Cha?

768
00:51:32,612 --> 00:51:33,571
Ms. Cha!

769
00:51:33,654 --> 00:51:34,906
-Huh?
-Oh, wow.

770
00:51:34,989 --> 00:51:38,284
-What are you so deep in thought about?
-Why? What?

771
00:51:39,285 --> 00:51:40,411
No-ah!

772
00:51:40,494 --> 00:51:42,038
-Hey, Na-ri.
-You're here.

773
00:51:42,830 --> 00:51:44,081
[exclaims]

774
00:51:45,875 --> 00:51:49,837
-Is this where the group blind date is?
-Yes. Why?

775
00:51:49,921 --> 00:51:51,964
Because I don't think I can do this,
you know.

776
00:51:52,048 --> 00:51:53,591
[No-ah exclaims]

777
00:51:53,674 --> 00:51:55,092
-Hey, grab her.
-Huh?

778
00:51:55,676 --> 00:51:58,888
What? Hey, guys. Wait, you guys.

779
00:51:59,388 --> 00:52:01,390
[soft jazz playing]

780
00:52:08,648 --> 00:52:11,817
Hello, everyone!
I'm Shin Na-ri, your host for tonight.

781
00:52:11,901 --> 00:52:12,902
Let's hear it.

782
00:52:14,654 --> 00:52:15,780
Okay, first of all,

783
00:52:15,863 --> 00:52:19,367
please introduce yourselves
to the people at your table.

784
00:52:19,450 --> 00:52:21,702
After that, feel free to move around,

785
00:52:21,786 --> 00:52:25,331
enjoy some wine,
and have all the conversations you want.

786
00:52:25,414 --> 00:52:27,875
All right, then. Hope you all have fun.

787
00:52:30,670 --> 00:52:32,588
[chuckles] Hello.

788
00:52:33,172 --> 00:52:34,590
So, we meet again.

789
00:52:34,674 --> 00:52:35,508
Sorry?

790
00:52:35,591 --> 00:52:36,884
Business card.

791
00:52:37,677 --> 00:52:38,928
Hello.

792
00:52:39,011 --> 00:52:40,429
I liked you at first sight.

793
00:52:40,513 --> 00:52:42,473
Can I please get your phone number?

794
00:52:42,556 --> 00:52:43,724
Oh. [chuckles]

795
00:52:44,225 --> 00:52:46,852
I'm very sorry, but I'm already engaged.

796
00:52:46,936 --> 00:52:48,813
Still, you never know
with people and relationships.

797
00:52:48,896 --> 00:52:50,523
KIM GI-SEUNG
INTERNAL MEDICINE SPECIALIST

798
00:52:50,606 --> 00:52:52,775
Oh! You're the one from back then.

799
00:52:52,858 --> 00:52:54,652
[chuckles] Oh. Hello again.

800
00:52:54,735 --> 00:52:57,989
Didn't you say you had a boyfriend?

801
00:52:58,072 --> 00:53:00,116
Or did you lie
because you weren't interested in me?

802
00:53:00,199 --> 00:53:01,283
No.

803
00:53:02,076 --> 00:53:05,246
I did have one, but I don't anymore.

804
00:53:05,329 --> 00:53:06,664
I told you, didn't I?

805
00:53:07,415 --> 00:53:08,708
You never know with relationships.

806
00:53:10,251 --> 00:53:13,087
You're right.
Life really is unpredictable.

807
00:53:13,796 --> 00:53:14,964
Do you like wine?

808
00:53:15,464 --> 00:53:16,298
Yes.

809
00:53:18,759 --> 00:53:20,219
-[patron] Thank you.
-Sure.

810
00:53:21,929 --> 00:53:23,180
Oh.

811
00:53:24,265 --> 00:53:25,558
Hello.

812
00:53:26,726 --> 00:53:31,188
-[chuckles] Uh, please don't mind me. Yes.
-[Ji-yoon] Thank you.

813
00:53:33,733 --> 00:53:35,151
So, do you know him?

814
00:53:35,651 --> 00:53:38,696
Well, yes, I've been here a few times
with a colleague.

815
00:53:38,779 --> 00:53:39,739
Ah.

816
00:53:42,867 --> 00:53:45,119
I should've given you
more work to do then.

817
00:53:46,037 --> 00:53:47,163
[sighs]

818
00:53:47,246 --> 00:53:49,206
Why did he say something like that?

819
00:53:51,751 --> 00:53:52,710
Let's see.

820
00:53:52,793 --> 00:53:57,048
-"Do you enjoy spending time alone?"
-[sighs]

821
00:53:57,131 --> 00:53:59,925
What on earth is that idiot doing?

822
00:54:02,762 --> 00:54:05,431
[Kee-tae] Goodbye! [laughing]

823
00:54:05,514 --> 00:54:08,768
-Okay, goodbye. Okay, goodbye. Thank you.
-[teacher] Goodbye.

824
00:54:08,851 --> 00:54:10,269
Oh.

825
00:54:10,352 --> 00:54:14,482
-All right. Han-yul, Han-gyeol, say hi.
-[both] Hello!

826
00:54:14,565 --> 00:54:17,359
-I'm sorry for asking you to come here.
-Not at all.

827
00:54:17,860 --> 00:54:19,278
I was the one who wanted to meet.

828
00:54:19,361 --> 00:54:22,656
-Daddy, I forgot my water bottle.
-And my jacket.

829
00:54:22,740 --> 00:54:23,574
Ah…

830
00:54:25,409 --> 00:54:26,494
Go right ahead.

831
00:54:26,577 --> 00:54:30,498
[sighs] All right, you stay here with
this gentleman and don't go anywhere.

832
00:54:30,581 --> 00:54:31,665
-Okay.
-Okay.

833
00:54:31,749 --> 00:54:33,793
Okay. All right. Thank you so much.

834
00:54:40,299 --> 00:54:41,759
Mister, who are you?

835
00:54:41,842 --> 00:54:42,885
I know.

836
00:54:42,968 --> 00:54:46,764
Dad called Mom earlier and said
he was meeting "Three-No-Man."

837
00:54:46,847 --> 00:54:50,392
-Right? You're Three-No-Man, right?
-Yes.

838
00:54:50,476 --> 00:54:52,895
Wow, then are you a superhero?

839
00:54:52,978 --> 00:54:53,979
Well, that's top secret.

840
00:54:54,063 --> 00:54:57,024
[shushing, laughing]

841
00:55:02,905 --> 00:55:04,949
[Kee-tae] All right, kids. Play safely.

842
00:55:08,452 --> 00:55:11,163
Yours was a proposal,
it wasn't an application.

843
00:55:11,247 --> 00:55:13,916
Oh, well, it's just an area
I've always been interested in.

844
00:55:13,999 --> 00:55:15,709
I apologize for overstepping.

845
00:55:16,293 --> 00:55:17,503
So you'd like to join,

846
00:55:17,586 --> 00:55:20,798
but your circumstances don't allow it?

847
00:55:20,881 --> 00:55:24,927
Well, as you can see, I'm not
in a position to join the task force.

848
00:55:29,431 --> 00:55:32,143
Listen, I owe you a favor, don't I?

849
00:55:32,226 --> 00:55:34,103
Oh, when I called Ji-yoon for you?

850
00:55:34,979 --> 00:55:36,147
Yes.

851
00:55:36,230 --> 00:55:38,607
Thanks to you,
I got an excellent colleague.

852
00:55:39,817 --> 00:55:40,651
Yeah.

853
00:55:41,318 --> 00:55:43,279
She's great, isn't she?

854
00:55:43,362 --> 00:55:46,949
And I believe Ms. Cha will also need
a good colleague like you by her side.

855
00:55:49,243 --> 00:55:51,287
You can work flexible hours.

856
00:55:51,370 --> 00:55:54,540
You're free to come in early
and leave early as well.

857
00:55:55,040 --> 00:55:56,834
Or work weekends, if you prefer.

858
00:55:56,917 --> 00:55:57,751
Really?

859
00:55:57,835 --> 00:56:00,379
You even have a master's degree in AI.

860
00:56:00,462 --> 00:56:01,755
It'd be a shame to waste that.

861
00:56:03,257 --> 00:56:04,425
Thank you so much.

862
00:56:04,508 --> 00:56:06,677
But there's one thing
that you should know first.

863
00:56:07,261 --> 00:56:10,055
If the project succeeds,
I'll be going back to the States.

864
00:56:12,266 --> 00:56:14,894
So I can't promise anything
about your position after that.

865
00:56:15,477 --> 00:56:18,147
However, I'll make sure it succeeds

866
00:56:18,230 --> 00:56:21,901
so that my team members will have
the power to choose for themselves,

867
00:56:21,984 --> 00:56:24,403
either by switching jobs or taking leave.

868
00:56:25,196 --> 00:56:29,533
Oh, so that's why there were rumors
about your team members disappearing

869
00:56:30,409 --> 00:56:31,660
without a trace.

870
00:56:32,244 --> 00:56:34,830
I'll do it. No, I-I mean I'll try.

871
00:56:36,498 --> 00:56:37,958
Glad to hear that.

872
00:56:38,042 --> 00:56:38,876
Yeah.

873
00:56:40,502 --> 00:56:44,006
[sighs] Oh, by the way,
I heard that Mr. Lee Young-hun

874
00:56:44,089 --> 00:56:46,759
is doing much better
since taking his leave of absence.

875
00:56:46,842 --> 00:56:50,262
-Were you the one who contacted him?
-No, I just passed along his number.

876
00:56:50,930 --> 00:56:51,764
And to whom?

877
00:56:52,431 --> 00:56:53,432
To Ms. Cha.

878
00:56:55,142 --> 00:56:59,146
She said she wanted to clear up
some of the misunderstandings about you.

879
00:57:02,441 --> 00:57:03,692
[phone buzzes]

880
00:57:08,280 --> 00:57:10,491
MESSAGE FROM LEE SEONG-MIN

881
00:57:10,574 --> 00:57:14,161
[Seong-min] Geez, you loser. Ji-yoon's
here on a group blind date right now.

882
00:57:22,628 --> 00:57:25,798
[Na-ri] So you're saying
you want to sit with that person, right?

883
00:57:26,632 --> 00:57:29,593
"Do you see yourself
getting married someday?"

884
00:57:31,053 --> 00:57:32,304
I'm not against marriage.

885
00:57:32,388 --> 00:57:35,057
-Then you should hurry.
-Why is that?

886
00:57:35,140 --> 00:57:37,059
You'll be turning 30 next year.

887
00:57:37,726 --> 00:57:41,647
When it comes to getting married,
men prefer women who are young

888
00:57:41,730 --> 00:57:44,358
because they want
fewer risks with childbirth.

889
00:57:46,652 --> 00:57:50,739
[sighs] "Can you stay friends with an ex?"

890
00:57:50,823 --> 00:57:54,493
[inhales deeply, sighs]
I don't think I could.

891
00:57:54,576 --> 00:57:55,786
What about you?

892
00:57:56,412 --> 00:57:59,039
Well, wouldn't that depend on

893
00:57:59,123 --> 00:58:02,334
what your relationship was like before
and how it ended?

894
00:58:04,169 --> 00:58:06,255
If you broke up on good terms…

895
00:58:06,880 --> 00:58:07,756
[Soo-jin] Si-woo.

896
00:58:12,052 --> 00:58:17,141
Thanks so much, for letting me see you
shine on stage one last time, Ga-eul.

897
00:58:18,559 --> 00:58:21,520
In that case,
I do think you could stay friends.

898
00:58:22,521 --> 00:58:25,316
Though, I don't feel ready to do that yet.

899
00:58:25,399 --> 00:58:26,984
[chuckles]

900
00:58:31,655 --> 00:58:34,033
WHAT MAKES YOUR HEART FLUTTER
THE MOST THESE DAYS?

901
00:58:34,116 --> 00:58:37,953
[lighthearted music playing]

902
00:58:42,541 --> 00:58:43,792
[Si-woo] You were just hiding,

903
00:58:43,876 --> 00:58:46,628
and then I thought to myself,
"I don't want to let this person go."

904
00:58:48,756 --> 00:58:50,424
I'm here from the future.

905
00:58:50,507 --> 00:58:51,884
This has already been released.

906
00:58:52,676 --> 00:58:54,511
[Ji-yoon] Sr. Associate Cha Ji-yoon
checking in.

907
00:58:54,595 --> 00:58:56,680
I'd like to apply for the task force.

908
00:58:59,558 --> 00:59:01,393
[Si-woo] Making one mistake is enough.

909
00:59:01,477 --> 00:59:03,187
Repeated mistakes are not mistakes.

910
00:59:03,270 --> 00:59:04,772
It shows their lack of competence.

911
00:59:05,689 --> 00:59:07,983
[Ji-yoon] Tell you what.
You can be the wind,

912
00:59:08,067 --> 00:59:09,568
and I'll be the sun.

913
00:59:11,612 --> 00:59:12,613
[Si-woo] The launch

914
00:59:14,114 --> 00:59:15,616
will be presented by Ms. Cha.

915
00:59:15,699 --> 00:59:17,993
If my manager is saying so,

916
00:59:18,077 --> 00:59:19,078
I suppose it does.

917
00:59:23,791 --> 00:59:28,337
Your gestures need to be
bolder and bigger.

918
00:59:30,255 --> 00:59:33,133
Well, that's a bit upsetting.

919
00:59:35,803 --> 00:59:37,179
Don't be sick.

920
00:59:37,763 --> 00:59:41,642
When you get nervous, remember…
[breathes deeply]

921
00:59:41,725 --> 00:59:42,976
…and you'll know the answer.

922
00:59:43,060 --> 00:59:45,270
-[Ji-yoon] Is that your sign, Coach?
-[Si-woo] Yes.

923
00:59:45,354 --> 00:59:46,522
[applause]

924
00:59:49,233 --> 00:59:50,317
WE'RE ON THE SAME TEAM, LOL

925
01:00:06,083 --> 01:00:08,919
CHA JI-YOON

926
01:00:10,462 --> 01:00:14,091
[Ji-yoon] So my feelings have
already grown this deep.

927
01:00:15,634 --> 01:00:18,846
WHAT MAKES YOUR HEART FLUTTER
THE MOST THESE DAYS?

928
01:00:25,769 --> 01:00:27,020
It's my new project

929
01:00:27,729 --> 01:00:28,730
at work.

930
01:00:32,526 --> 01:00:33,610
[door opens]

931
01:00:36,280 --> 01:00:38,115
-[door closes]
-[whirring]

932
01:00:50,878 --> 01:00:53,630
WELCOME BACK HOME

933
01:01:06,602 --> 01:01:07,603
CHA JI-YOON

934
01:01:07,686 --> 01:01:11,315
[No-ah] Ms. Cha told me the task force
has a great driver,

935
01:01:11,398 --> 01:01:12,941
so you just need to step on the gas

936
01:01:13,025 --> 01:01:17,070
without having to worry about whether
you're headed in the right direction.

937
01:01:18,030 --> 01:01:22,242
[Kee-tae] She said she wanted to clear up
some of the misunderstandings about you.

938
01:01:27,664 --> 01:01:29,291
YOU HAVE 1 NEW VIDEO
WOULD YOU LIKE TO VIEW?

939
01:01:29,374 --> 01:01:30,834
Hmm. Play it.

940
01:01:38,550 --> 01:01:39,760
Is this it?

941
01:01:42,763 --> 01:01:44,014
Or not?

942
01:01:45,140 --> 01:01:48,560
Wow. You do a lot of things, don't you?

943
01:01:50,270 --> 01:01:55,317
[sighs] It must be really hard
to have such a neat-freak owner.

944
01:01:56,193 --> 01:01:57,778
[Ji-yoon chuckles]

945
01:02:48,287 --> 01:02:50,289
[soft jazz playing]

946
01:02:52,040 --> 01:02:53,750
Why didn't you go to the second round?

947
01:02:53,834 --> 01:02:57,504
He told me I should marry soon
if I wanted children.

948
01:02:57,588 --> 01:02:58,422
What?

949
01:02:58,505 --> 01:03:01,049
Marriage felt
like the easiest destination.

950
01:03:01,133 --> 01:03:03,552
Now, it just seems like
an imaginary island.

951
01:03:03,635 --> 01:03:05,679
Of course it is.

952
01:03:05,762 --> 01:03:09,016
Because it's not somewhere
you can go by yourself.

953
01:03:09,099 --> 01:03:11,768
[laughing] You're right.

954
01:03:17,983 --> 01:03:19,651
-[sighs]
-[phone buzzes, chimes]

955
01:03:24,281 --> 01:03:25,657
[Kee-tae] Did you know?

956
01:03:25,741 --> 01:03:27,200
If the project succeeds,

957
01:03:27,284 --> 01:03:29,661
Mr. Kang is heading back to the US office.

958
01:03:31,872 --> 01:03:34,541
[Ji-yoon] What do you mean?
Who told you that?

959
01:03:35,876 --> 01:03:37,961
[Kee-tae]
I heard it from Mr. Kang himself.

960
01:03:38,045 --> 01:03:40,756
The task force is just a temporary team.

961
01:03:40,839 --> 01:03:43,467
It's not a big deal,
but I thought you should know.

962
01:03:43,550 --> 01:03:45,677
-Is there something wrong?
-No. [chuckles]

963
01:03:45,761 --> 01:03:48,388
I just need to go to the restroom.

964
01:04:05,572 --> 01:04:08,825
WOULD YOU BET ON A LOVE
WITH HIGH ODDS OF FAILURE?

965
01:04:14,581 --> 01:04:15,749
[footsteps approaching]

966
01:04:17,167 --> 01:04:19,294
Hey. She just left a moment ago.

967
01:04:19,795 --> 01:04:21,797
[gentle music playing]

968
01:04:48,281 --> 01:04:51,034
[Ji-yoon] Twenty-year-old me
never hesitated.

969
01:04:51,827 --> 01:04:55,038
I wasn't afraid of a one-sided love
that offered me nothing in return

970
01:04:55,122 --> 01:04:57,040
and when love found me unexpectedly,

971
01:04:57,124 --> 01:05:00,460
I never kept score.
I just wanted it to last forever.

972
01:05:01,128 --> 01:05:02,671
But the person I am now

973
01:05:03,380 --> 01:05:04,715
knows the great pain that comes

974
01:05:04,798 --> 01:05:09,261
from the sharp edges
of broken pieces of a failed love.

975
01:05:10,887 --> 01:05:14,057
And yet, these feelings
have started again.

976
01:05:18,895 --> 01:05:20,981
Can I really step onto the mound again

977
01:05:21,064 --> 01:05:24,735
for a game with low odds
and a predictable ending?

978
01:05:53,847 --> 01:05:55,140
[line ringing]

979
01:05:56,641 --> 01:05:58,143
Yes, this is Kang Si-woo.

980
01:05:58,727 --> 01:05:59,770
Should I come to you?

981
01:06:13,909 --> 01:06:15,660
No, you shouldn't come.

982
01:06:20,582 --> 01:06:22,042
Because I want to…

983
01:06:22,918 --> 01:06:24,211
leave the task force.

984
01:07:13,552 --> 01:07:17,180
[Ji-yoon] If there's one thing I've
learned from my past relationship,

985
01:07:19,015 --> 01:07:22,936
it's that I shouldn't even start
a relationship that is doomed to fail.

986
01:07:23,895 --> 01:07:25,522
What a way to draw the line.

987
01:07:26,147 --> 01:07:28,567
I'm not his cousin.
I'm his ex he dated for seven years.

988
01:07:28,650 --> 01:07:31,194
And this jerk cheated on me with you.

989
01:07:31,987 --> 01:07:33,697
[Si-woo] You can tell me now.

990
01:07:33,780 --> 01:07:35,824
What's the real reason
you want to leave the task force?

991
01:07:35,907 --> 01:07:37,701
[Kee-tae] I wanted to feign ignorance.

992
01:07:37,784 --> 01:07:39,786
I'm just not wired that way,
so I'll just go ahead and ask.

993
01:07:40,287 --> 01:07:42,789
[grunts] There's someone in here!

994
01:07:42,873 --> 01:07:44,291
[Si-woo] I was worried about you.

995
01:07:44,374 --> 01:07:45,500
Why?

996
01:07:45,584 --> 01:07:47,210
[Si-woo] Because to me, Ms. Cha…

